raw: * The data array is a special array used in the data binding context of
* qooxdoo. It does not extend the native array of JavaScript but its a wrapper
* for it. All the native methods are included in the implementation and it
* also fires events if the content or the length of the array changes in
* any way. Also the .length property is available on the array.
* This class does not need to be disposed, unless you set the autoDisposeItems
* property to true and want the items to be disposed.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The data array is a special array used in the data binding context of qooxdoo. It does not extend the native array of JavaScript but its a wrapper for it. All the native methods are included in the implementation and it also fires events if the content or the length of the array changes in any way. Also the .length property is available on the array. This class does not need to be disposed, unless you set the autoDisposeItems property to true and want the items to be disposed.
